President Barack Obama has sent a letter to the House and Senate leadership, as well as the chairmen and ranking members of House and Senate committees, regarding the Report to Congress on Afghanistan-Pakistan Policy. This is the second report submitted under section 1117 of the Supplemental Appropriations Act, 2009. The report provides an update on the policy implemented in Afghanistan and Pakistan since the last report in March 2010. The Obama Administration completed a thorough policy review in November 2009 and announced a new approach at West Point on December 1, 2009. General David Petraeus was appointed to lead military efforts in Afghanistan. The report covers the period ending June 30, 2010, with updates on the assessment since then. The President emphasizes the importance of the successful implementation of this policy to the nation's interests.